Steps to Reproduce:
1. write a string literal like
       let content =
   `import React, { Component} from 'react';
   import './${name}.css';
   class ${name} extends Component {
   render() {
       return (
           <div className="${name}">
               main Component
           </div>
       );
   }
   }

export default ${name};`

the editor does not recognize the string literal for collapsing it, 
instead it collapses on the line with class. 
this is also fine but it should recognize that it is a string template.

even worse the collapse mechanisme outside also seems to be mismatched then.

